backend/spikes/route_engine_algorithmic/runs/

# Mock-Document Corpus — Layer 2 default policy: keep the directory empty so
# real, personally-identifying PDFs never accidentally land in the repo.
# DUS-31 Slice 8 reverses the policy for GENERATOR-EMITTED trip directories —
# every committed entry lives under a `<NN>-<descriptor>` slug carved by the
# integration trip-bundle generator. The leak guard
# (`corpus/pdf/validate.py::_leak_guard_check`) enforces the
# "top-level-files-still-forbidden" half of the policy.
corpus/pdf/layer2/*
!corpus/pdf/layer2/.gitkeep
!corpus/pdf/layer2/[0-9][0-9]-*/
